  "prompt": "Why did Thor's hammer shake in the movie \u2018Avengers: Age of Ultron\u2019 when Captain America tried to lift it?",
  "response": "In 'Avengers: Age of Ultron', Thor's hammer, Mjolnir, shakes when Captain America attempts to lift it because it is enchanted. The enchantment allows only the worthy to wield it, and when Steve Rogers, aka Captain America, tries to lift Mjolnir, it reacts as a way to test his worthiness. \n\nWhile Captain America is deemed worthy to some extent (as indicated by the shaking of the hammer), he ultimately does not lift it. This moment highlights the strong bond of respect and friendship between Thor and Captain America, and also underscores the theme of worthiness that is central to Mjolnir's significance in the Marvel Universe. Captain America's slight movement of the hammer serves as a subtle hint that he is considered worthy in the eyes of Mjolnir, even if he doesn't completely lift it.",
